Q4: What happens if I am terminated before the vesting period ends?\nA: Vesting may be accelerated depending on the circumstances surrounding your termination. Please contact Compensation & Benefits for more information.\n',
'prompt': '''I need a concise summary of how new hires receive their restricted stock unit awards.'''}
 New hires receive their restricted stock unit (RSU) awards through a two-step process involving currency conversion and valuation against the company's stock price. Firstly, the RSU grant target value, specified in euros or another foreign currency in the offer letter, gets converted into U.S. dollars using the 9-month average exchange rate up until the first business day of the Hooli fiscal quarter that aligns with the employee's start date. This conversion isn't needed if the initial offer letter was already in U.S. dollars. Post conversion, the total dollar amount is divided by the average closing stock price of Hooli over the final 21 trading days of the corresponding month, rounding down to the nearest whole unit. For example, a new hire starting on May 2nd, 2022, with a grant target of €200,000 would get approximately 1,300 RSUs after these calculations. These grants become visible in the employee's Schwab account during the second week of the subsequent month and are typically awarded on the eleventh business day of the next month. In case of early termination, vesting acceleration depends on specific circumstances and can be discussed further with the Compensation & Benefits department.

